REST API Target
│
├─ 1. Reconnaissance            — Identify API existence
│   ├─ DNS / Subdomains         — api.*, v1.*, dev.*
│   ├─ ping                    — Host reachability
│   └─ TLS / Cert Info         — API host metadata
│
├─ 2. Enumeration              — Discover API surface
│   ├─ Open Ports              — 80, 443, 8080, 8443
│   ├─ Base Paths              — /api, /v1, /v2
│   └─ Versioning              — Deprecated endpoints
│
├─ 3. Mapping                  — Understand API structure
│   ├─ Endpoints               — /users, /orders
│   ├─ HTTP Methods            — GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
│   ├─ Content Types           — JSON, XML
│   └─ Status Codes            — Behavior clues
│
├─ 4. Input Discovery          — Identify controllable input
│   ├─ Query Parameters        — ?id=, ?filter=
│   ├─ Path Parameters         — /users/{id}
│   ├─ JSON Body Fields        — request payload
│   └─ Headers                 — Auth, custom headers
│
├─ 5. Authentication Analysis  — Access control model
│   ├─ API Keys                — Static secrets
│   ├─ JWT Tokens              — Claims & expiry
│   ├─ OAuth Flows             — Token issuance
│   └─ Session Handling        — Stateless vs stateful
│
├─ 6. Authorization Testing    — Who can do what
│   ├─ Object‑level access     — ID‑based controls
│   ├─ Function‑level access   — Admin vs user
│   └─ Tenant isolation        — Multi‑tenant risk
│
├─ 7. Weakness Detection       — Identify security gaps
│   ├─ Broken Object Level Auth (BOLA)
│   ├─ Excessive Data Exposure
│   ├─ Mass Assignment
│   └─ Rate‑limit weaknesses
│
├─ 8. Exploitation Validation  — Confirm impact
│   ├─ Unauthorized data access
│   ├─ Privilege escalation
│   └─ Business logic abuse
│
├─ 9. Traffic & Behavior       — Runtime observation
│   ├─ Request / response flow
│   ├─ Error patterns
│   └─ Token reuse behavior
│
└─ 10. Automation & Scaling    — Repeat across APIs
    ├─ Endpoint lists
    ├─ Spec‑driven scanning
    └─ Continuous monitoring

